& [DisciplineRules] is the overlay governance result
  + [rule_001] is use known-zero ordinates as reference labels, never as labels that certify local extrema
  + [rule_002] is read sparse vertical resonance as a comparison surface, not a primary detector
  + [rule_003] is read dense Lambda overlay heat as phasor and prime-power inspection pressure, not identity
  + [rule_004] is require agreement across layers to ask better questions, not to claim causation
  + [rule_005] is treat cutoff stability and cross-window stability as finite repeatability only
  + [rule_006] is block new overlay computation unless a source names a measured object such as cross-layer landmark displacement, stability class, or phasor-layer contribution

& [Inference] is the current whole-field meaning
  + [positive_meaning] is the overlay field now has a disciplined reading order from reference labels to sparse landmarks to dense Lambda heat to half-plane boundary checks
  + [negative_meaning] is no overlay alignment collapses into a single RH identity because the candidate fields are dense, metric-dependent, cutoff-sensitive, and reference-guided
  + [curiosity_pressure] is reference-near heat remains meaningful periphery because it appears in both sparse and dense surfaces, but the correct response is bounded comparison, not proof inference
  + [restraint_result] is landmark-overlay work is now refined enough for orientation; no new overlay scan or visualization is justified from existing records alone

& [NextOrientation] is the restrained forward rail
